text: Myosin light chain, phosphorylatable, fast skeletal muscle is a protein that in humans is encoded by the MYLPF gene. It is located on chromosome 16 in humans. Myosin light chain, phosphorylatable, fast skeletal muscle is an integral part of the myosin light chain structure found in human muscles. == References == == Further reading == * * * * Category:EF-hand-containing proteins
title: MYLPF
